00:23:31,207 --> 00:23:33,667
"We had a meeting last month
that we updated the budget,

639
00:23:33,667 --> 00:23:36,090
"but we forgot to tell
the FinOps team about it."

640
00:23:36,090 --> 00:23:38,010
But instead, you get into a place where,

641
00:23:38,010 --> 00:23:39,180
especially with AI agents,

642
00:23:39,180 --> 00:23:41,670
where you can actually look at an anomaly,

643
00:23:41,670 --> 00:23:43,320
and by the time it hits your desk,

644
00:23:43,320 --> 00:23:45,630
you're getting the full
context of why it happened,

645
00:23:45,630 --> 00:23:48,840
what's happening, and then
finally, how to remediate it.

646
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:50,760
And today, remediation
is one of those things

647
00:23:50,760 --> 00:23:52,890
that we don't really offer, right?

648
00:23:52,890 --> 00:23:53,917
We say, "Hey, there's an issue.

649
00:23:53,917 --> 00:23:56,340
"Go take a look at it, figure it out."

650
00:23:56,340 --> 00:23:58,330
And oftentimes, there's
a lot of time spent

651
00:23:58,330 --> 00:24:00,030
trying to figure this out, right?

652
00:24:00,030 --> 00:24:02,400
Either be it, is it a code change?

653
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:03,750
Was it that we had a lot more volume,

654
00:24:03,750 --> 00:24:05,670
and it was a good thing,
like I said earlier?

655
00:24:05,670 --> 00:24:07,270
Was it something else
causing this entirely?

656
00:24:07,270 --> 00:24:09,540
Could it have been that
the savings plan ran out,

657
00:24:09,540 --> 00:24:11,370
and so now the cost is spiking,

658
00:24:11,370 --> 00:24:12,267
and that is a reason for it,

659
00:24:12,267 --> 00:24:14,850
and not that EC2 is all
of a sudden 40% higher

660
00:24:14,850 --> 00:24:17,250
than it was last month, right?

661
00:24:17,250 --> 00:24:20,250
So being able to now
remediate it in a way that,

662
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:22,560
in fact, why even stop there?

663
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:24,300
Instead of just showing you what it is

664
00:24:24,300 --> 00:24:27,270
that you should fix, oftentimes,
I feel like in security,

665
00:24:27,270 --> 00:24:28,890
we would be able to patch
something immediately.

666
00:24:28,890 --> 00:24:31,410
We give access to a lot
of our security tools

